s original, Lévy takes a bird’s-eye view of the most consequential historical event of our time and proposes a way to defend human society from threats to our collective future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCOVID-19 (Disease). 0aEpidemics. 0aMass mediaxSocial aspects. 0aPhilosophy, Frenchy21st century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Essays.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020z978311069231040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300257380423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300257380.jpg  a978-3-11-069231-0  YUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070482-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPHb2020